<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="113" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1802,2007]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,1439]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="113" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1946,1971]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
While the female of 
<taxonomicName box="[584,753,1948,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emiratensis">
<emphasis box="[584,753,1948,1971]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">H. emiratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still unknown, the male differs from the other two 
<emphasis box="[1409,1429,1948,1971]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">H</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[160,250,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Tkalcua</emphasis>
) species by the distinctly shorter proboscis with the second segment of the labial palpus being only 
<number lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="113" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3– 1.4</number>
x as long as the first segment (
<figureCitation box="[524,608,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[576,608,152,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Additional diagnostic characters are the more extended white pilosity on tergum 
<number box="[238,252,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
, which laterally extends till the base of the horizontal part of tergum 
<number box="[1044,1058,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1074,1159,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[1128,1159,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
), a row of white bristles along the carina that separates the declivous from the horizontal part of tergum 
<number box="[1083,1097,224,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1116,1202,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[1171,1202,224,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
), the densely haired tergum 
<number box="[236,252,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="5.0">5</number>
, and the shorter body length not exceeding 
<quantity box="[741,802,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" unit="mm" value="5.0">5mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Description.</emphasis>
MALE: Body length 
<quantity box="[591,680,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[691,751,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Head</emphasis>
: Head about 
<number box="[903,952,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="0.85">0.85</number>
x as long as wide. Distance between lateral ocellus and preoccipital ridge about 
<number box="[556,590,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x as long as ocellar diameter. Maximal width of genal area 
<number box="[1252,1336,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="0.55" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.6</number>
x as long as maximal width of compound eye. Second segment of labial palpus 
<number box="[948,1032,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4</number>
x as long as first segment (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1424,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Brightened parts of mandible yellow. Antenna yellowish-brown except for the first two segments, which are black. Head covered with dense and appressed white pilosity except for the vertex, which is beset with single long white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[227,317,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[285,317,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Punctation" authorityName="Punctation" box="[342,603,476,501]" class="Crustacea" family="Crustacea" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[342,462,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: Punctation
</taxonomicName>
of scutum and scutellum dense with interspaces rarely exceeding the diameter of one to one and a half punctures. Basal area of propodeum densely shagreened with many longitudinal carinulae (
<figureCitation box="[272,359,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,359,548,572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Propodeal triangle polished in its lower half. 
<taxonomicName box="[913,1035,549,572]" class="Crustacea" family="Crustacea" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
covered with dense white pilosity except for its ventral side, the central parts of scutum and scutellum, the propodeal triangle and the lateral surface of the propodeum, which are unhaired or beset with single white hairs. Tegula, stigma and veins of wings yellow. Femur of all legs apically with dense tuft of white hairs. Outer surface of hind tibia, to a lesser extent also of fore and middle tibia, covered with dense and appressed white pilosity. Middle femur medially broadened on its ventral side. Inner spur of hind leg yellow, its apex curved upwards at an angle of about 
<number box="[1045,1073,730,755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="45.0">45</number>
º. 
<emphasis box="[1094,1210,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Metasoma</emphasis>
: Punctation of terga fine and dense with interspaces rarely exceeding the diameter of one puncture. Declivous anterior part of tergum 
<number box="[1422,1436,767,791]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
broadly concave, polished, unhaired and unpunctured, separated from the horizontal part of tergum 
<number box="[1295,1309,803,827]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
by a weak transverse carina (
<figureCitation box="[356,441,838,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[409,441,839,863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Marginal zones of terga 
<number box="[736,778,839,863]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
reddish and with long, dense and uninterrupted white hair bands (
<figureCitation box="[234,319,874,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[288,319,875,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Appressed white pilosity on lateral sides of tergum 
<number box="[934,948,875,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
almost reaching base of horizontal part of tergum 
<number box="[239,253,911,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[271,357,910,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[325,357,911,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Carina separating anterior concavity of tergum 
<number box="[923,937,911,935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
from its horizontal part with row of strong white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[291,375,946,971]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[344,375,947,971]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Discs of terga 
<number box="[560,602,946,971]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
covered with appressed white pilosity. Tergum 
<number box="[1142,1156,946,971]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="6.0">6</number>
with yellowish marginal zone, its apical margin with distinct lateral angle. Tergum 
<number box="[836,850,984,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="7.0">7</number>
yellowish, completely hidden below tergum 
<number box="[1378,1394,982,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="6.0">6</number>
, its surface densely haired except for a narrow unhaired apical zone; its apical margin evenly rounded and with loose fringe of rather long white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[539,626,1054,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[594,626,1055,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Sterna 
<number box="[728,770,1054,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
unmodified and all of about the same length, their apical margins more or less straight. Apical margins of sterna 
<number box="[766,808,1091,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
with rather dense white hair band, of sternum 
<number box="[1324,1338,1090,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="5.0">5</number>
sparsely ciliated with short white hairs and of sternum 
<number box="[667,681,1126,1151]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="6.0">6</number>
with dense fringe of yellowish-white hairs. Base of sternum 
<number box="[1365,1379,1126,1151]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="6.0">6</number>
with a pair of large translucent flaps. Gonoforceps yellowish, with weak longitudinal keel and more or less parallelsided except for its apical forth, which is narrowed on the outer side (
<figureCitation box="[926,1010,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,371,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[152,1435,371,1518]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 19 – 24. 19: Hoplitis paralias, clypeus of female. 20: Hoplitis zandeni, clypeus of female. 21: Hoplitis zandeni, tergum 7 and genitalia of male. 22: Hoplitis emiratensis, head and proboscis of male. 23: Hoplitis emiratensis, metasoma of male. 24: Hoplitis emiratensis, tergum 7 and genitalia of male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259698/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number box="[978,1010,1199,1223]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
); its apex, outer and inner side as well as underside with numerous long white bristles.
</paragraph>
